# DNS Debug Project Rules

## Purpose

FastAPI DNS diagnostic service running inside a Docker container. Observes DNS through embedded resolver `127.0.0.11`. Diagnoses search domains, ndots thresholds, query noise, and latency under load. Optional MTR TCP diagnostics and optional Web UI observability layer.

## Non-negotiable constraints

1. Do not modify `/etc/resolv.conf` at runtime or in Dockerfile.
2. Do not add `dns:` or `dns_search:` to `docker-compose.yml`.
3. Do not use `network_mode: host`.
4. Do not add sidecar DNS (unbound, bind, dnsmasq).
5. Do not claim heuristic cache metrics (`dns_debug_possible_cached_response_total`) represent real Docker DNS cache.
6. Preserve stable core API paths and Prometheus metric names.
7. Do not delete or rename core DNS invariants without an explicit user request.
8. Do not propose architecture that breaks embedded Docker DNS assumptions.
9. Do not substitute container-local resolver (`127.0.0.11`) with host loopback or public DNS.

## Mandatory observability model

These must remain in code, metrics, and documentation:

- Prometheus metrics (`/metrics`) — always enabled
- EDNS analytics breakdown (edns0–edns5)
- Garbage / noisy query accounting (six `NoiseType` values)
- Cache visibility as heuristic (with disclaimer)
- Per-resolver / per-`resolve_mode` analysis
- MTR observability (when `MTR_ENABLED`)
- Background test execution
- Optional Web UI gated by `DNS_DEBUG_UI_ENABLED`

## Preferred style

- Minimal, focused diffs — change only what the task requires
- Match existing module patterns (`ResolveSpec`, async stats store, pydantic models)
- Use exact metric names from `app/metrics.py`
- Keep search probes (`is_search_probe=True`) separate from primary queries in logic and docs
- Test behavior assumes standard Docker bridge + `127.0.0.11`
- Treat Web UI as optional layer — core engine must work with `DNS_DEBUG_UI_ENABLED=false`
- Prefer simple observability UI on top of built-in backend — no heavy frontend frameworks without explicit request
- Do not mix operational noise metrics with business/application metrics
- Always distinguish useful DNS queries from garbage/noisy DNS queries

## DNS implementation guidance

- Resolve modes: `system`, `absolute_fqdn`, `ndots:N` (via `ndots_values`)
- `expand_work_items` drives the test matrix
- Noise classification in `dns_runner._classify_noise` — six `NoiseType` values
- Analytics in `ndots_analytics.build_test_analytics` and `build_diagnosis`
- Summaries via `stats_store.build_summary`
- Do not treat DNS cache behavior as an unimportant detail — document heuristics honestly

Key extension points: `dns_runner._resolve`, `_classify_noise`, `expand_work_items`; `stats_store.record_attempt`, `build_summary`; `metrics.record_query`, `set_test_analytics`.

## Web UI guidance

- Gated by `DNS_DEBUG_UI_ENABLED` — when false, no UI routes, static mounts, or `/api/ui/*`
- Default `DNS_DEBUG_UI_READONLY=true` — no POST/DELETE from browser; control tests via core API
- Mount under `DNS_DEBUG_UI_BASE_PATH` (default `/dns-debug`) on same FastAPI app
- Env vars: `DNS_DEBUG_UI_PORT`, `DNS_DEBUG_UI_BIND`, `DNS_DEBUG_UI_REFRESH_SECONDS`, `DNS_DEBUG_UI_I18N_*`
- **i18n:** all new user-facing UI strings via `app/ui/static/i18n/en.json` + `ru.json` and `t()` / `data-i18n` — never hardcode in templates/JS
- Verify RU layout impact at 1024–1440px when changing labels or filters
- Prefer Jinja2 + vanilla JS + Chart.js; no heavy SPA build pipeline
- UI reads from `stats_store`, `mtr_store`, metrics registry, and historical persistence (`app/db/` PostgreSQL when `DNS_DEBUG_DB_ENABLED=true`, else `data/snapshots/` JSON files)
- Never imply heuristic cache UI cards show real Docker DNS cache hits
- UI is for developer, SRE, QA, and analyst — not a required dependency for tests
- Any Web UI change must update UI panel descriptions in `AGENT.md` and `debugging-checklist.md`
- Dashboard supports **live**, **historical**, and **compare** view modes — see `AGENT.md` UI spec
- Historical mode uses in-memory event buffer (`from`/`to`) or persisted snapshots (PostgreSQL with **7-day retention** when DB enabled, or `SNAPSHOT_*` file mode)
- Compare mode uses server-side `/api/ui/compare` deltas — never client-only delta math for KPIs

## QA / UX gates

Major UI work requires role-appropriate review before the task is complete:

| Change type | Required perspective |
|-------------|---------------------|
| Major UI feature or layout | QA acceptance perspective (`qa-ui` skill) |
| Major UX / IA change | UX designer perspective (`ux-designer` skill) |
| New dashboard section | UX clarity check (purpose, states, microcopy) |
| Historical mode | QA checklist — retention, stale, empty states |
| Compare mode | **Both** `qa-ui` and `ux-designer` skills + `debugging-checklist.md` |
| Visual changes | State coverage for loading, empty, error, stale, retention exceeded |
| History features | Retention and empty-state design (`ux-designer`); truncation honesty (`qa-ui`) |
| Live UX v2 | `global_status` rollup, KPI trends, auto-refresh toggle, 3-tier sub-nav |
| Pre-release UX audit | Stage 2 UX audit deliverable (`ux-designer` skill) |
| Responsive review | QA 8-width checklist; laptop breakage (1024–1440px) = P1 blocker |
| Chart/layout QA | Chart readability and layout hierarchy at laptop widths |
| Release readiness | No open P0/P1; Stages 1–4 complete; docs synced; release artifact updated |

**Incomplete:** visual or behavioral UI changes without state coverage; history/compare without retention messaging; compare without delta verification; UI shipped without pre-release workflow (Stages 1–3); open P1 responsive laptop/tablet breakage; UI/UX/i18n/workflow changes without `CHANGELOG.md` and `docs/releases/X.Y.Z.md`.

Release playbook: [`docs/releases/README.md`](docs/releases/README.md). See `.cursor/rules/qa-ux-gates.mdc` for enforcement rules and doc sync requirements.

