Do not remove EDNS breakdown, per-resolver analysis, or MTR diagnostics from the observability model.

## API endpoints

**Core:** `/health`, `/resolver`, `/tests`, `/tests/{id}`, `/tests/{id}/diagnosis`, `/summary`, `/metrics`, `/mtr`, `/mtr/runs`

**UI** (when `DNS_DEBUG_UI_ENABLED=true`, under `{DNS_DEBUG_UI_BASE_PATH}/api/ui/`):

`/overview`, `/dns-latency`, `/edns`, `/errors`, `/garbage`, `/cache`, `/records`, `/load`, `/mtr`, `/rankings`, `/snapshots`, `/snapshots/{id}`, `/compare`, `/snapshots`, `/snapshots/{id}`, `/compare`

**HTML:** `GET {DNS_DEBUG_UI_BASE_PATH}/` (e.g. `/dns-debug/`)

## PostgreSQL persistence rules

- Historical data defaults to **local PostgreSQL** with **7-day retention** (`DNS_DEBUG_DB_RETENTION_DAYS`)
- Retention cleanup must run automatically (startup + periodic); do not bypass silently
- No new history feature without retention-aware UX and docs sync
- Schema/config/storage changes require `AGENT.md`, skills, rules, and release doc updates
- `DNS_DEBUG_DB_ENABLED=false` preserves file-based snapshot mode for backward compatibility
- Do not expose PostgreSQL port externally by default; credentials only via env

## Trade-offs and compatibility

- Prefer minimal, backward-compatible changes
- When in doubt, preserve current observability richness
- Document trade-offs explicitly in commits and AI docs
- Do not break UI JSON contracts without explicit approval
